JDK / JRE /JVM

*JVM runs Java bytecode.
*JRE=JVM + Libraries + Other Components (JAVA RUNTIME ENVIRONMENT)
*JDK=JRE + Compilers + Debuggers (JAVA DEVELOPMENT KIT)

*Computer understand only 1 & 0, these are basic instruction.

1.java code(write once run any time)
2.compiled
3.Bytecode(intermediate code,common for all OS)
4.  BYTECODE ---------->Windows JVM(EXECUTION)------------>windows instructions

JAVA CLASS AND OBJECT
*Class is template, can use this template to create multiple instance of class(OBJECT)

>BLOCK OF CODE CLASS
-METHODS.
-DATA.

jshell> class country{
   ...> }
|  created class country

jshell> country india = new country()
india ==> country@3c0f93f1

jshell> country usa = new country()
usa ==> country@31610302

